    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (80.03) serving as our undisputed anchor. Facing Chris Paddack (xERA 4.64), **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a massive 15% efficiency boost tied to the SP skill delta, further augmented by wind blowing out. While **Andy Pages** (69.83) also profiles as a high-floor start against Paddack, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (65.71) remains our most reliable pillar of production. Despite a tough matchup against Suarez, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** maintains a strong score due to park factor advantages and an excellent 0.384 xwOBA, proving that even against decent arms, his elite contact quality keeps him firmly in the lineup.\n\nOur bench strategy remains disciplined, prioritizing high-efficiency ceilings in a 5x5 Roto environment where game caps are precious. The most difficult decision today was bypassing **Nolan Schanuel** (49.48), whose matchup against Kay (xERA 5.57) initially looked inviting. However, the combination of a lower-tier batting order spot (#7) and a 38% rain risk significantly dragged down his utility, leading us to favor **Marcell Ozuna** (54.77) and **Jackson Merrill** (50.36) to ensure we don't bleed category potential. **Miguel Vargas** (53.46) remains a start despite the \u26a0\ufe0f rain risk; we are monitoring his status closely, as his scoring profile relies heavily on favorable SP matchups that could be negated if the game is significantly delayed or shortened.\n\nFinally, while we hunt for stolen bases to close the gap in the scarcest category, we are wary of the defensive positioning of our opponents today. **Jackson Merrill** faces an elite hold pitcher, which caps his ceiling for base-stealing opportunities regardless of his favorable spot in the order. We are maintaining a high threshold for starters; with **Gunnar Henderson** and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** sidelined by team off-days, our active roster must bridge the gap through sheer volume of high-quality at-bats from **